 “A lot of people are wary of (Quiroga’s) shock measures. Paz’s appeal is strong in rural areas and among some older voters — the kinds of people who might have supported MAS if it had fielded a real candidate,” said Gustavo Flores-Macías, dean of the School of Public Policy at the University of Maryland. 

























